(52, 1, '2015-07-05 23:49:07', '2015-07-05 23:49:07', 'Each year more than 400,000 Australians undergo treatment for skin cancer, with more than 11,500 cases of Melanoma diagnosed <sup>1</sup>. In 2011 there were more than 2000 deaths due to Skin Cancer<sup>1</sup>\r\n\r\nAlere offer programs that can:\r\n\r\n<ol> <li>Detect suspicious lesions</li>\r\n<li>Identify individuals at high risk</li> \r\n<li>Encourage employees to regularly check their skin</li> </ol>\r\n\r\n<strong>Skin Cancer Screening</strong>\r\nAlere has performed skin checks to over 50,000 patients Australia wide â€“ including checks in every state and territory, in every capital city, and in hundreds of regional and remote locations. Experienced and skilled General Practitioners conduct thorough skin checks on-site and make immediate recommendations on treatment and follow-up actions.\r\n\r\n<strong>Skin Cancer Risk Education</strong>\r\nAlere use an evidence-based risk prediction tool to provide an individual risk of developing a melanoma. Participants are provided with their individual risk rating and education on sun safety practices. Participants also view the sun damage to their skin using a specialised lamp designed to highlight the importance of regular self-checks. The Skin Cancer Risk Assessment can be incorporated into a more comprehensive Health Assessment.\r\n\r\n<p><a href="mailto:info@smghealth.com.au">Contact our team</a> for more information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><sup>1 Cancer Council 2013, </sup><a href="http://www.cancer.org.au/policy-and-advocacy/position-statements/sun-smart/"><sup>http://www.cancer.org.au/policy-and-advocacy/position-statements/sun-smart/</sup></a></p>', 'Skin Cancer Screening', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'skin-cancer-screening', '', '', '2015-07-07 03:08:43', '2015-07-07 03:08:43', '', 46, 'http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/?page_id=52', 0, 'page', '', 0),
