(236, 1, '2015-07-06 06:36:53', '2015-07-06 06:36:53', 'Welcome to our Wellbeing Challenges.\r\nHelping your people to live well, work well and perform better. (GRAPHICS)\r\nEmployers are becoming increasingly aware of the importance and value of\r\nstaff wellbeing. The benefits of a healthy workforce are many.\r\nAll organisations, regardless of size, can now take a proactive approach\r\ntowards staff wellbeing with our â€˜Wellbeing Challengesâ€™.\r\nOur new, innovative concept, engages employees in a low cost, web-driven\r\nprogramme of activities. The programme helps people to make small changes\r\nto their own Wellbeing through achievable team challenges.\r\nThe challenges are short &amp; simple, allowing the participants to remain focused\r\non achievable goals.\r\nEach challenge lasts 4 weeks and is delivered with a support package that is\r\nproven to motivate employees of all ages and abilities.\r\nItâ€™s fun, competitive, focused team building, designed specifically to tackle\r\nemployee health and wellbeing issues.\r\nFor a fixed fee per challenge, with no restrictions on the number of\r\nparticipants, our web portal allows organisations to run team based, wellbeing\r\nchallenges, efficiently and effectively.\r\nParticipating teams can track their progress on our web portal and prizes are\r\nawarded to those individuals that have made a special effort towards\r\nimproving their personal, team and corporate health and wellbeing.\r\nThe Wellbeing Challenges on-line interface can be branded to reflect your\r\nown organisations corporate identity. A full suite of marketing and\r\ncommunication materials is also available to support the challenges.\r\nThe Wellbeing Challenges require minimal time investment but are capable of\r\ndelivering significant behavioral shifts within a team or workforce.\r\nOur challenges are fun, easy to administer and are proven to engage staff\r\nand deliver results.\r\nWhether theyâ€™re a beginner or an avid fitness enthusiast, Wellbeing\r\nChallenges will help boost your peopleâ€™s energy, improve their health and\r\nencourage them to enjoy the benefits of an active lifestyle.\r\nOur team challenge concepts are proven to be successful. We have\r\nimplemented challenges for many organisations with spectacular results.\r\nLetâ€™s take a brief look at some of our current Wellbeing Challengesâ€¦\r\nGet Active Challenge\r\nThere is no doubt that moving more and sitting less is good for your overall\r\nhealth. This 4-week challenge aims to motivate your people to include more\r\nexercise in each day.\r\nOur challenge is simple;\r\nTeams of up to 5 people record their daily activity levels. At the end of each\r\nweek a Team manager registers the teams total minutes of exercise on the\r\nWellbeing Challenges web portal.\r\nAt the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the most minutes is the\r\nwinner!\r\nThe challenge encourages participents to work together to create a daily\r\nexercise plan and share ideas for group exercise activities.\r\nParticipants will benefit from an overall increase in fitness levels, happiness\r\nand self esteem, as well as helping to reduce the risk of developing diabetes,\r\nheart disease, weight gain, osteoporosis and cancer.\r\nWeight Loss Challenge\r\nThe weight loss challenge aims to help reduce weight, specifically targeting\r\nâ€˜apple shapedâ€™ people who are already known to be at the greatest risk of\r\ndeveloping ill health or disease in future.\r\nOur challenge is simple\r\nTeams of up to 5 people aim to lose 1-2lbs per week, per participant.\r\nThe teams record their weekly weight loss. At the end of each week a Team\r\nmanager registers the teams total weight loss on the Wellbeing Challenges\r\nweb portal.\r\nAt the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the greatest weight loss is\r\nthe winner!\r\nParticipants will benefit from feeling healthier, having more energy and an\r\nincreased sense of self-confidence.\r\nWe do not advocate any strange diets or eating plans. The Wellbeing\r\nChallenge advises participants to follow standard healthy eating guidelines\r\nand participate in moderate exercise.\r\nHydration Challenge\r\nWater is an essential nutrient of life. Adequate hydration is the key to short\r\nand long term healthy wellbeing. Drinking little and often throughout the day\r\ncan help us stay healthy and keep us alert.\r\nOur bodies lose approximately 2.5 litres of water each day. Even mild\r\ndehydration adversely affects both mental and physical performance.\r\nThe hydration challenge encourages employees to drink more fluids per day\r\nand teaches them how to recognise the signs of de-hydration.\r\nOur challenge is simple:\r\nThe Hydration Challenge is a points based challenge. Participants aim to\r\ncollect 2 hydration points per day over the 4 week programme.\r\nAt the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the most hydration points is\r\nthe winner! Prizes are awarded to the winning team and the highest scoring\r\nindividuals.\r\nSimply drinking 6 to 8 glasses of water or fluid each day can help to reduce\r\nfatigue, increase energy levels and provide greater focus and concentration.\r\nHealthy Eating Challenge\r\nThe healthy eating challenge encourages employees to eat a healthy\r\nbalanced diet every day.\r\nWhen it comes to a healthy diet, balance is the key to getting it right. This\r\nmeans eating a wide variety of foods in the right proportions, and consuming\r\nthe right amount of food and drink to achieve and maintain a healthy body\r\nweight.\r\nOur challenge is simple:\r\nThe Healthy Eating Challenge is a points based challenge. By following our\r\nrecommended healthy eating guidelines, participants aim to collect 6 healthy\r\neating points per day totaling a maximum of 42 per week.\r\nYour team manager registers your weekly points total on the Wellbeing\r\nChallenge web portal. At the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the\r\nmost points is the winner!\r\nThe Healthy Eating challenge encourages participants to achieve a balanced\r\ndiet by following both our food and drink guidelines and our 6 daily resilience\r\nhabits.\r\nCycling Challenge\r\nCycling is one of the most ergonomically efficient ways to exercise and is\r\nopen to all levels of ability.\r\nThe workplace cycle challenge aims to encourage employees to improve\r\nfitness through cycling.\r\nOur challenge is simple\r\nThe challenge is based on cycling miles. Teams of 1 to 5 people record how\r\nmany miles their team cycle over the 4 week programme. The team with the\r\nhighest number of cycle miles after 4 weeks is the winner!\r\nYour team manager registers the teams total cycle miles on the Wellbeing\r\nChallenges web portal each week. The winning team and individuals receive\r\nprizes for the most miles cycled.\r\nThis challenge is not about how fast you are.\r\nThe workplace cycle challenge is about encouraging employees to increase\r\ntheir physical activity, improve their fitness while having some fun on 2\r\nwheels!\r\nEnergy 4 Life Challenge\r\nOur energy levels dictate what we do and how well we do it. Expectation to\r\ndeliver has never been higher and yet 75% of the working population wakes\r\nup exhausted each day.\r\nThe Energy 4 Life challenge aims to boost energy levels to help employees\r\nget the most out of life, both at home and at work.\r\nThis challenge involves thinking about meals, sleep, movement, rest,\r\nrecuperation and work life balance. Our challenge is simple;\r\nParticipants are given 7 â€˜energy habitsâ€™ to follow each day, including moderate\r\nexercise, healthy eating and relaxation exercises.\r\nEach day, you collect one â€˜energy pointâ€™ for each habit you follow. Over each\r\nweek, you collect â€˜energy pointsâ€™ for your team.\r\nAt the end of each week, your team manager registers the teamâ€™s score on\r\nWellbeing Challenges web portal.\r\nAt the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the most points is the\r\nwinner!\r\nMaking simple daily choices such as eating regularly will not only boost your\r\nenergy, it will rejuvenate your life. Most people who have joined the challenge\r\nfeel fitter, more positive, have higher energy levels and feel more engaged at\r\nwork and at home.', 'Wellbeing Challenges', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'wellbeing-challenges', '', '', '2015-07-06 06:41:27', '2015-07-06 06:41:27', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/?page_id=236', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(237, 1, '2015-07-06 06:36:53', '2015-07-06 06:36:53', 'Welcome to our Wellbeing Challenges.\r\nHelping your people to live well, work well and perform better. (GRAPHICS)\r\nEmployers are becoming increasingly aware of the importance and value of\r\nstaff wellbeing. The benefits of a healthy workforce are many.\r\nAll organisations, regardless of size, can now take a proactive approach\r\ntowards staff wellbeing with our â€˜Wellbeing Challengesâ€™.\r\nOur new, innovative concept, engages employees in a low cost, web-driven\r\nprogramme of activities. The programme helps people to make small changes\r\nto their own Wellbeing through achievable team challenges.\r\nThe challenges are short &amp; simple, allowing the participants to remain focused\r\non achievable goals.\r\nEach challenge lasts 4 weeks and is delivered with a support package that is\r\nproven to motivate employees of all ages and abilities.\r\nItâ€™s fun, competitive, focused team building, designed specifically to tackle\r\nemployee health and wellbeing issues.\r\nFor a fixed fee per challenge, with no restrictions on the number of\r\nparticipants, our web portal allows organisations to run team based, wellbeing\r\nchallenges, efficiently and effectively.\r\nParticipating teams can track their progress on our web portal and prizes are\r\nawarded to those individuals that have made a special effort towards\r\nimproving their personal, team and corporate health and wellbeing.\r\nThe Wellbeing Challenges on-line interface can be branded to reflect your\r\nown organisations corporate identity. A full suite of marketing and\r\ncommunication materials is also available to support the challenges.\r\nThe Wellbeing Challenges require minimal time investment but are capable of\r\ndelivering significant behavioral shifts within a team or workforce.\r\nOur challenges are fun, easy to administer and are proven to engage staff\r\nand deliver results.\r\nWhether theyâ€™re a beginner or an avid fitness enthusiast, Wellbeing\r\nChallenges will help boost your peopleâ€™s energy, improve their health and\r\nencourage them to enjoy the benefits of an active lifestyle.\r\nOur team challenge concepts are proven to be successful. We have\r\nimplemented challenges for many organisations with spectacular results.\r\nLetâ€™s take a brief look at some of our current Wellbeing Challengesâ€¦\r\nGet Active Challenge\r\nThere is no doubt that moving more and sitting less is good for your overall\r\nhealth. This 4-week challenge aims to motivate your people to include more\r\nexercise in each day.\r\nOur challenge is simple;\r\nTeams of up to 5 people record their daily activity levels. At the end of each\r\nweek a Team manager registers the teams total minutes of exercise on the\r\nWellbeing Challenges web portal.\r\nAt the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the most minutes is the\r\nwinner!\r\nThe challenge encourages participents to work together to create a daily\r\nexercise plan and share ideas for group exercise activities.\r\nParticipants will benefit from an overall increase in fitness levels, happiness\r\nand self esteem, as well as helping to reduce the risk of developing diabetes,\r\nheart disease, weight gain, osteoporosis and cancer.\r\nWeight Loss Challenge\r\nThe weight loss challenge aims to help reduce weight, specifically targeting\r\nâ€˜apple shapedâ€™ people who are already known to be at the greatest risk of\r\ndeveloping ill health or disease in future.\r\nOur challenge is simple\r\nTeams of up to 5 people aim to lose 1-2lbs per week, per participant.\r\nThe teams record their weekly weight loss. At the end of each week a Team\r\nmanager registers the teams total weight loss on the Wellbeing Challenges\r\nweb portal.\r\nAt the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the greatest weight loss is\r\nthe winner!\r\nParticipants will benefit from feeling healthier, having more energy and an\r\nincreased sense of self-confidence.\r\nWe do not advocate any strange diets or eating plans. The Wellbeing\r\nChallenge advises participants to follow standard healthy eating guidelines\r\nand participate in moderate exercise.\r\nHydration Challenge\r\nWater is an essential nutrient of life. Adequate hydration is the key to short\r\nand long term healthy wellbeing. Drinking little and often throughout the day\r\ncan help us stay healthy and keep us alert.\r\nOur bodies lose approximately 2.5 litres of water each day. Even mild\r\ndehydration adversely affects both mental and physical performance.\r\nThe hydration challenge encourages employees to drink more fluids per day\r\nand teaches them how to recognise the signs of de-hydration.\r\nOur challenge is simple:\r\nThe Hydration Challenge is a points based challenge. Participants aim to\r\ncollect 2 hydration points per day over the 4 week programme.\r\nAt the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the most hydration points is\r\nthe winner! Prizes are awarded to the winning team and the highest scoring\r\nindividuals.\r\nSimply drinking 6 to 8 glasses of water or fluid each day can help to reduce\r\nfatigue, increase energy levels and provide greater focus and concentration.\r\nHealthy Eating Challenge\r\nThe healthy eating challenge encourages employees to eat a healthy\r\nbalanced diet every day.\r\nWhen it comes to a healthy diet, balance is the key to getting it right. This\r\nmeans eating a wide variety of foods in the right proportions, and consuming\r\nthe right amount of food and drink to achieve and maintain a healthy body\r\nweight.\r\nOur challenge is simple:\r\nThe Healthy Eating Challenge is a points based challenge. By following our\r\nrecommended healthy eating guidelines, participants aim to collect 6 healthy\r\neating points per day totaling a maximum of 42 per week.\r\nYour team manager registers your weekly points total on the Wellbeing\r\nChallenge web portal. At the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the\r\nmost points is the winner!\r\nThe Healthy Eating challenge encourages participants to achieve a balanced\r\ndiet by following both our food and drink guidelines and our 6 daily resilience\r\nhabits.\r\nCycling Challenge\r\nCycling is one of the most ergonomically efficient ways to exercise and is\r\nopen to all levels of ability.\r\nThe workplace cycle challenge aims to encourage employees to improve\r\nfitness through cycling.\r\nOur challenge is simple\r\nThe challenge is based on cycling miles. Teams of 1 to 5 people record how\r\nmany miles their team cycle over the 4 week programme. The team with the\r\nhighest number of cycle miles after 4 weeks is the winner!\r\nYour team manager registers the teams total cycle miles on the Wellbeing\r\nChallenges web portal each week. The winning team and individuals receive\r\nprizes for the most miles cycled.\r\nThis challenge is not about how fast you are.\r\nThe workplace cycle challenge is about encouraging employees to increase\r\ntheir physical activity, improve their fitness while having some fun on 2\r\nwheels!\r\nEnergy 4 Life Challenge\r\nOur energy levels dictate what we do and how well we do it. Expectation to\r\ndeliver has never been higher and yet 75% of the working population wakes\r\nup exhausted each day.\r\nThe Energy 4 Life challenge aims to boost energy levels to help employees\r\nget the most out of life, both at home and at work.\r\nThis challenge involves thinking about meals, sleep, movement, rest,\r\nrecuperation and work life balance. Our challenge is simple;\r\nParticipants are given 7 â€˜energy habitsâ€™ to follow each day, including moderate\r\nexercise, healthy eating and relaxation exercises.\r\nEach day, you collect one â€˜energy pointâ€™ for each habit you follow. Over each\r\nweek, you collect â€˜energy pointsâ€™ for your team.\r\nAt the end of each week, your team manager registers the teamâ€™s score on\r\nWellbeing Challenges web portal.\r\nAt the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the most points is the\r\nwinner!\r\nMaking simple daily choices such as eating regularly will not only boost your\r\nenergy, it will rejuvenate your life. Most people who have joined the challenge\r\nfeel fitter, more positive, have higher energy levels and feel more engaged at\r\nwork and at home.', 'Wellbeing Challenges', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '236-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-06 06:36:53', '2015-07-06 06:36:53', '', 236, 'http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/236-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
