(262, 1, '2015-07-06 07:47:05', '2015-07-06 07:47:05', 'Corporate flu vaccinations are a cost-effective method of avoiding the suffering of influenza. Studies have shown that employees who have had a flu vaccination experienced a 90% reduction in the risk of contracting influenza and 44% fewer visits to their GP1.\r\n\r\nWith over 20 years of industry experience, Alere provides high quality, best practice corporate flu vaccination programs. Benefits of our corporate flu vaccinations include:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>flu vaccinations can be delivered nationally and onsite</li>\r\n<li>professional service and flu vaccination program management</li>\r\n<li>dedicated flu vaccination coordinators</li>\r\n<li>innovative marketing support</li>\r\n<li>convenient online booking system</li>\r\n<li>guaranteed supply of flu vaccination vaccines</li>\r\n<li>cold chain management compliance with flu vaccinationsâ€™ safety management practices</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nProtect your employees, your community and the productivity of your company with corporate flu vaccinations.\r\n\r\n<p><sub>1<sup></sup>Nicol KL et al. The effectiveness of vaccination against influenza in healthy, working adults. New England Journal of Medicine 1995: 333: 889-893</sub></p>', 'Flu Vaccinations', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '50-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-06 07:47:05', '2015-07-06 07:47:05', '', 50, 'http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/50-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(263, 1, '2015-07-06 07:47:34', '2015-07-06 07:47:34', 'Each year more than 400,000 Australians undergo treatment for skin cancer, with more than 11,500 cases of Melanoma diagnosed <sup>1</sup>. In 2011 there were more than 2000 deaths due to Skin Cancer<sup>1</sup>\r\n\r\nAlere offer programs that can:\r\n\r\n<ol> <li>Detect suspicious lesions</li>\r\n<li>Identify individuals at high risk</li> \r\n<li>Encourage employees to regularly check their skin</li> </ol>\r\n\r\n<strong>Skin Cancer Screening</strong>\r\nAlere has performed skin checks to over 50,000 patients Australia wide â€“ including checks in every state and territory, in every capital city, and in hundreds of regional and remote locations. Experienced and skilled General Practitioners conduct thorough skin checks on-site and make immediate recommendations on treatment and follow-up actions.\r\n\r\n<strong>Skin Cancer Risk Education</strong>\r\nAlere use an evidence-based risk prediction tool to provide an individual risk of developing a melanoma. Participants are provided with their individual risk rating and education on sun safety practices. Participants also view the sun damage to their skin using a specialised lamp designed to highlight the importance of regular self-checks. The Skin Cancer Risk Assessment can be incorporated into a more comprehensive Health Assessment.\r\n\r\n<p><a href="mailto:au.enquiries@alere.com">Contact our team</a> for more information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><sup>1 Cancer Council 2013, </sup><a href="http://www.cancer.org.au/policy-and-advocacy/position-statements/sun-smart/"><sup>http://www.cancer.org.au/policy-and-advocacy/position-statements/sun-smart/</sup></a></p>', 'Skin Cancer Screening', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '52-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-06 07:47:34', '2015-07-06 07:47:34', '', 52, 'http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/52-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
