 having more energy and an\r\nincreased sense of self-confidence.\r\nWe do not advocate any strange diets or eating plans. The Wellbeing\r\nChallenge advises participants to follow standard healthy eating guidelines\r\nand participate in moderate exercise.\r\nHydration Challenge\r\nWater is an essential nutrient of life. Adequate hydration is the key to short\r\nand long term healthy wellbeing. Drinking little and often throughout the day\r\ncan help us stay healthy and keep us alert.\r\nOur bodies lose approximately 2.5 litres of water each day. Even mild\r\ndehydration adversely affects both mental and physical performance.\r\nThe hydration challenge encourages employees to drink more fluids per day\r\nand teaches them how to recognise the signs of de-hydration.\r\nOur challenge is simple:\r\nThe Hydration Challenge is a points based challenge. Participants aim to\r\ncollect 2 hydration points per day over the 4 week programme.\r\nAt the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the most hydration points is\r\nthe winner! Prizes are awarded to the winning team and the highest scoring\r\nindividuals.\r\nSimply drinking 6 to 8 glasses of water or fluid each day can help to reduce\r\nfatigue, increase energy levels and provide greater focus and concentration.</p>\r\n<h2>Healthy Eating Challenge</h2>\r\n<p>\r\nThe healthy eating challenge encourages employees to eat a healthy\r\nbalanced diet every day.\r\nWhen it comes to a healthy diet, balance is the key to getting it right. This\r\nmeans eating a wide variety of foods in the right proportions, and consuming\r\nthe right amount of food and drink to achieve and maintain a healthy body\r\nweight.\r\nOur challenge is simple:\r\nThe Healthy Eating Challenge is a points based challenge. By following our\r\nrecommended healthy eating guidelines, participants aim to collect 6 healthy\r\neating points per day totaling a maximum of 42 per week.\r\nYour team manager registers your weekly points total on the Wellbeing\r\nChallenge web portal. At the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the\r\nmost points is the winner!\r\nThe Healthy Eating challenge encourages participants to achieve a balanced\r\ndiet by following both our food and drink guidelines and our 6 daily resilience\r\nhabits.\r\n<h2>Cycling Challenge</h2>\r\n<p>\r\nCycling is one of the most ergonomically efficient ways to exercise and is\r\nopen to all levels of ability.\r\nThe workplace cycle challenge aims to encourage employees to improve\r\nfitness through cycling.\r\nOur challenge is simple\r\nThe challenge is based on cycling miles. Teams of 1 to 5 people record how\r\nmany miles their team cycle over the 4 week programme. The team with the\r\nhighest number of cycle miles after 4 weeks is the winner!\r\nYour team manager registers the teams total cycle miles on the Wellbeing\r\nChallenges web portal each week. The winning team and individuals receive\r\nprizes for the most miles cycled.\r\nThis challenge is not about how fast you are.\r\nThe workplace cycle challenge is about encouraging employees to increase\r\ntheir physical activity, improve their fitness while having some fun on 2\r\nwheels!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Energy 4 Life Challenge</h2>\r\n<p>Our energy levels dictate what we do and how well we do it. Expectation to\r\ndeliver has never been higher and yet 75% of the working population wakes\r\nup exhausted each day.\r\nThe Energy 4 Life challenge aims to boost energy levels to help employees\r\nget the most out of life, both at home and at work.\r\nThis challenge involves thinking about meals, sleep, movement, rest,\r\nrecuperation and work life balance. Our challenge is simple;\r\nParticipants are given 7 â€˜energy habitsâ€™ to follow each day, including moderate\r\nexercise, healthy eating and relaxation exercises.\r\nEach day, you collect one â€˜energy pointâ€™ for each habit you follow. Over each\r\nweek, you collect â€˜energy pointsâ€™ for your team.\r\nAt the end of each week, your team manager registers the teamâ€™s score on\r\nWellbeing Challenges web portal.\r\nAt the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the most points is the\r\nwinner!\r\nMaking simple daily choices such as eating regularly will not only boost your\r\nenergy, it will rejuvenate your life. Most people who have joined the challenge\r\nfeel fitter, more positive, have higher energy levels and feel more engaged at\r\nwork and at home.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Physical Health section', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '282-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-06 08:46:01', '2015-07-06 08:46:01', '', 282, 'http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/282-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
