(348, 1, '2015-07-07 03:10:20', '2015-07-07 03:10:20', 'Alereâ€™s education sessions increase health awareness while using behaviour change models to increase the likelihood of health improvements. Our range of seminars are tailored to meet the different requirements of each specific audience and are facilitated by experts in their field.\r\n\r\nOur seminars range from short toolbox presentations to full day workshops.\r\n\r\nAlere has a variety of sessions within the following areas:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Achieving Peak Wellbeing</li>\r\n	<li><a href="/au/en/health-solutions/health-management/InterventionPrograms/SmokingCessation.html#mainpar_text">Smoking Cessation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="/au/en/health-solutions/health-management/InterventionPrograms/MentalHealthSleepandFatigueManagement.html#mainpar_text">Mental Health</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="/au/en/health-solutions/health-management/InterventionPrograms/MentalHealthSleepandFatigueManagement.html#mainpar_text">Fitness &amp; Physical Activity</a></li>\r\n	<li>Nutrition &amp; Cooking Demonstrations</li>\r\n	<li><a href="/au/en/health-solutions/health-management/InterventionPrograms/WeightManagement.html#mainpar_text">Weight Management</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="/au/en/health-solutions/health-management/InterventionPrograms/InjuryPrevention.html#mainpar_text">Injury Prevention</a></li>\r\n	<li>Disease Prevention</li>\r\n	<li><a href="/au/en/health-solutions/health-management/InterventionPrograms/MentalHealthSleepandFatigueManagement.html#mainpar_text">Sleep &amp; Fatigue</a></li>\r\n	<li>Family &amp; Gender Health</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="mailto:info@smghealth.com.au">Contact our team</a> for more information.</p>', 'Seminars & Workshops', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '54-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-07 03:10:20', '2015-07-07 03:10:20', '', 54, 'http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/54-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(349, 1, '2015-07-07 03:13:55', '2015-07-07 03:13:55', '<div class="col-md-12">\r\n<h2>Wellbeing Challenges.</h2>\r\n<p class="text-justify">Welcome to our Wellbeing Challenges.Helping your people to live well, work well and perform better. (GRAPHICS)Employers are becoming increasingly aware of the importance and value of staff wellbeing. The benefits of a healthy workforce are many.All organisations, regardless of size, can now take a proactive approach towards staff wellbeing with our â€˜Wellbeing Challengesâ€™.Our new, innovative concept, engages employees in a low cost, web-driven programme of activities. The programme helps people to make small changes to their own Wellbeing through achievable team challenges.<img class="img-thumbnail img-responsive alignright wp-image-294 size-medium" src="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/wellbeing_challenges-300x300.jpg" alt="wellbeing_challenges" width="300" height="300" />\r\nThe challenges are short &amp; simple, allowing the participants to remain focused on achievable goals.Each challenge lasts 4 weeks and is delivered with a support package that is proven to motivate employees of all ages and abilities.Itâ€™s fun, competitive, focused team building, designed specifically to tackle employee health and wellbeing issues. For a fixed fee per challenge, with no restrictions on the number of participants, our web portal allows organisations to run team based, wellbeing challenges, efficiently and effectively. Participating teams can track their progress on our web portal and prizes are awarded to those individuals that have made a special effort towards improving their personal, team and corporate health and wellbeing.\r\nThe Wellbeing Challenges on-line interface can be branded to reflect your own organisations corporate identity.A full suite of marketing and communication materials is also available to support the challenges. The Wellbeing Challenges require minimal time investment but are capable of delivering significant behavioral shifts within a team or workforce. Our challenges are fun, easy to administer and are proven to engage staff and deliver results. Whether theyâ€™re a beginner or an avid fitness enthusiast, Wellbeing Challenges will help boost your peopleâ€™s energy, improve their health and encourage them to enjoy the benefits of an active lifestyle. Our team challenge concepts are proven to be successful. We have implemented challenges for many organisations with spectacular results. Letâ€™s take a brief look at some of our current Wellbeing Challengesâ€¦</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Get Active Challenge</h2>\r\n<p class="text-justify">There is no doubt that moving more and sitting less is good for your overall health. This 4-week challenge aims to motivate your people to include more exercise in each day.\r\n<strong> Our challenge is simple;</strong>\r\nTeams of up to 5 people record their daily activity levels. At the end of each week a Team manager registers the teams total minutes of exercise on the Wellbeing Challenges web portal.At the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the most minutes is the winner!The challenge encourages participents to work together to create a daily exercise plan and share ideas for group exercise activities. Participants will benefit from an overall increase in fitness levels, happiness and self esteem, as well as helping to reduce the risk of developing diabetes, heart disease, weight gain, osteoporosis and cancer.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Weight Loss Challenge</h2>\r\n<p class="text-justify">The weight loss challenge aims to help reduce weight, specifically targeting â€˜apple shapedâ€™ people who are already known to be at the greatest risk of developing ill health or disease in future. Our challenge is simple Teams of up to 5 people aim to lose 1-2lbs per week, per participant. The teams record their weekly weight loss. At the end of each week a Team manager registers the teams total weight loss on the Wellbeing Challenges web portal. At the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the greatest weight loss is the winner! Participants will benefit from feeling healthier, having more energy and an increased sense of self-confidence. We do not advocate any strange diets or eating plans. The Wellbeing Challenge advises participants to follow standard healthy eating guidelines and participate in moderate exercise.Hydration Challenge Water is an essential nutrient of life. Adequate hydration is the key to short and long term healthy wellbeing. Drinking little and often throughout the day can help us stay healthy and keep us alert. Our bodies lose approximately 2.5 litres of water each day. Even mild dehydration adversely affects both mental and physical performance.\r\nThe hydration challenge encourages employees to drink more fluids per day and teaches them how to recognise the signs of de-hydration. Our challenge is simple: The Hydration Challenge is a points based challenge. Participants aim to collect 2 hydration points per day over the 4 week programme.\r\nAt the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the most hydration points is the winner! Prizes are awarded to the winning team and the highest scoring\r\nindividuals. Simply drinking 6 to 8 glasses of water or fluid each day can help to reduce fatigue, increase energy levels and provide greater focus and concentration.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Healthy Eating Challenge</h2>\r\n<p class="text-justify">The healthy eating challenge encourages employees to eat a healthy balanced diet every day. When it comes to a healthy diet, balance is the key to getting it right. This means eating a wide variety of foods in the right proportions, and consuming the right amount of food and drink to achieve and maintain a healthy bodyweight. Our challenge is simple:The Healthy Eating Challenge is a points based challenge. By following our recommended healthy eating guidelines, participants aim to collect 6 healthy eating points per day totaling a maximum of 42 per week. Your team manager registers your weekly points total on the Wellbeing Challenge web portal. At the end of the 4-week challenge the team with the most points is the winner! The Healthy Eating challenge encourages participants to achieve a balanced diet by following both our food and drink guidelines and our 6 daily resilience habits.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Cycling Challenge</h2>\r\n<p class="text-justify">Cycling is one of the most ergonomically efficient ways to exercise and is open to all levels of ability. The workplace cycle challenge aims to encourage employees to improve fitness through cycling. Our challenge is simple The challenge is based on cycling miles. Teams of 1 to 5 people record how\r\nmany miles their team cycle over the 4 week programme. The team with the highest number of cycle miles after 4 weeks is the winner! Your team manager registers the teams total cycle miles on the Wellbeing Challenges web portal each week. The winning team and individuals receive prizes for the most miles cycled. This challenge is not about how fast you are. The workplace cycle challenge is about encouraging employees to increase\r\ntheir physical activity, improve their fitness while having some fun on 2 wheels!</p>\r\n</div>', 'Physical Health section', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '282-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-07 03:13:55', '2015-07-07 03:13:55', '', 282, 'http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/282-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
