(355, 1, '2015-07-07 04:04:33', '2015-07-07 04:04:33', '<div class="col-md-12 sen_me_tem">\r\n<img src="" alt="" title="">\r\n<h2>Brief Resume: BRIAN MELTZER	</h2>\r\n<p><i>B.Com(NZ)  M.Ec (Monash) </i></p>\r\n<p>Brian was chief economist of ICI Australia (now Orica) 1979 -1983 prior to a 25 year career in investment banking.\r\nHe was appointed Director of a Federal government licensed Innovations Investment Fund  as well as a Federal government licensed technology incubator. He has been a Non Executive Director or Advisor in a number of private companies in the area of HR, Health and Aged Care, Software, Entertainment and Finance. He worked with the management of the current SMG Health team during the 15 years that he co-owned OSA Group (later PPC) â€“ a provider of mental health services to large corporates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brian is currently a Director of Prana Biotechnology, a company publically listed on both the ASX and Nasdaq, and has served for many years as Chairman of its Audit & Risk committee as well as of its Remuneration committee.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>He has regularly taken the role of mentor and business angel in a number of start-ups as well as in mature private businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>From 1994 Brian has been a Director of the Australia Israel Chamber of Commerce and since 2011 he has been Chairman of Independence Australia which provides services and products to the Disability and Aged Care sectors.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-12 sen_me_tem">\r\n<img src="" alt="" title="">\r\n<h2>Ian Shakespeare 	</h2>\r\n<p><i>MBA BSc MAPS  and CEO of SMG Health </i></p>\r\n<p>Ian Shakespeare MBA BSc MAPS  and CEO of SMG Health is a Psychologist & Management Consultant with over 25 yearsâ€™ experience assisting organisations in improving productivity through the implementation of integrated holistic health and wellbeing programs to businesses across the Asia Pacific region. He strongly believes in the importance of individual employees taking responsibility for their own health coupled with need of organisations in creating and maintaining work environments conducive to this. Ian is confident expert staff (physical and mental health) at SMG coupled with their passion and commitment to improved health and productivity outcomes will be critical in achieving our charter: Healthy workplaces = Healthy outcomes \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-md-12 sen_me_tem">\r\n<img src="" alt="" title="">\r\n<h2>Jaqui Bond  	</h2>\r\n<p><i>B.App.Sc (Physio), Grad. Dip. Hlth, Research Meth., MPH. </i></p>\r\n<p>Jaquiâ€™s passion is leading a team to deliver quality driven programs which assist people to be the best they can be. Â She does this well from experience borne across 25 years in the healthcare industry. She started in clinical physiotherapy and over the years became business owner, strategic program developer and implementer, Â and team leader. She holds a Masters in Public Health from Columbia University (New York) which provides her with a solid framework for health services management to ensure that not only are the programs right for your employees but also right for your organisation to achieve the goals it seeks.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="col-md-12 sen_me_tem">\r\n<img src="" alt="" title="">\r\n<h2>PHILOMINA GUNASEKERA</h2>\r\n<p><i>Institute of Chartered Accountants - Australia\r\nChartered Institute of Management Accountants - UK\r\nAssociation of Accounting Technicians â€“ UK </i></p>\r\n<p>Twenty five years of work experience in diversified organisations (Public listed, SMEs) which includes Manufacturing, Stock broking, Real Estate, Financial services, Employee Wellness and Other Professional service sectors as a Senior Member and Head of Finance.<p>\r\n<p>\r\nWorked for A4e Group of Companies as the Finance Director (CFO) and Company Secretary since March 2013. Prior to the above role, worked as the CFO, Director for PPC Worldwide for 11 years (A United Health Group Company, NYSE entity). Key roles included Overseeing all financial activities (whilst overseeing a team) that entailed budgeting, forecasting, month-end reporting, audit, tax, procurement, ERP implementation, mergers and acquisitions. A key part of the role involved aligning finance closely with the business to assist with company performance / activities, strategic direction and business growth. \r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 'Senior Management Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '334-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-07 04:04:33', '2015-07-07 04:04:33', '', 334, 'http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/334-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
