ssisting organisations in improving productivity through the implementation of integrated holistic health and wellbeing programs to businesses across the Asia Pacific region. He strongly believes in the importance of individual employees taking responsibility for their own health coupled with need of organisations in creating and maintaining work environments conducive to this. Ian is confident expert staff (physical and mental health) at SMG coupled with their passion and commitment to improved health and productivity outcomes will be critical in achieving our charter: Healthy workplaces = Healthy outcomes\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-12 sen_me_tem">\r\n\r\n<img title="" alt="" />\r\n<h2>Jaqui Bond</h2>\r\n<i>B.App.Sc (Physio), Grad. Dip. Hlth, Research Meth., MPH. </i>\r\n\r\nJaquiâ€™s passion is leading a team to deliver quality driven programs which assist people to be the best they can be. Â She does this well from experience borne across 25 years in the healthcare industry. She started in clinical physiotherapy and over the years became business owner, strategic program developer and implementer, Â and team leader. She holds a Masters in Public Health from Columbia University (New York) which provides her with a solid framework for health services management to ensure that not only are the programs right for your employees but also right for your organisation to achieve the goals it seeks.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-12 sen_me_tem">\r\n\r\n<img title="" alt="" />\r\n<h2>PHILOMINA GUNASEKERA</h2>\r\n<i>Institute of Chartered Accountants - Australia\r\nChartered Institute of Management Accountants - UK\r\nAssociation of Accounting Technicians â€“ UK </i>\r\n\r\nTwenty five years of work experience in diversified organisations (Public listed, SMEs) which includes Manufacturing, Stock broking, Real Estate, Financial services, Employee Wellness and Other Professional service sectors as a Senior Member and Head of Finance.\r\n\r\nWorked for A4e Group of Companies as the Finance Director (CFO) and Company Secretary since March 2013. Prior to the above role, worked as the CFO, Director for PPC Worldwide for 11 years (A United Health Group Company, NYSE entity). Key roles included Overseeing all financial activities (whilst overseeing a team) that entailed budgeting, forecasting, month-end reporting, audit, tax, procurement, ERP implementation, mergers and acquisitions. A key part of the role involved aligning finance closely with the business to assist with company performance / activities, strategic direction and business growth.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Senior Management Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '334-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-07 04:22:11', '2015-07-07 04:22:11', '', 334, 'http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/334-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
