(372, 1, '2015-07-07 04:23:38', '2015-07-07 04:23:38', '<strong>Empower Your Spine </strong>\r\n\r\nBack and neck pain is consistently in the top 3 self-reported medical conditions of office workers significantly impacting employeesâ€™ performance. Three major causes of back and neck pain in office workers are:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Inappropriate workstation set up causing poor posture</li>\r\n	<li>Prolonged computer use.</li>\r\n	<li>Lack of strength on core muscle groups</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe Empower Your Spine program is a 12 week program which goes straight to spine of the problem and offers your employees the education, tools and strategies to prevent, and reduce back and neck pain in the workplace.\r\n\r\n<strong>Winter Health Package </strong>\r\n\r\nAs temperatures drop and days get shorter it can be difficult to maintain our healthy lifestyle. SMG Health offers your employees education and strategies to keep healthy throughout the winter months.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Time4Action: Weight Loss Program </strong>\r\n\r\nThe Time4Action program empowers your employees to take charge of their lifestyle and get back on track to optimal health. The program focuses on dietary intake, physical activity, and patterns of behaviours. Accompanied by the EMPOWER health coaching program, weekly meal plans and including optional workshops, seminars and additional coaching, this program will equip employees with the knowledge and skills to initiate and maintain positive changes.\r\n\r\n<strong>Rise and Shine Package </strong>\r\n\r\nSleep is vital to the day to day functioning and balance of our physical, mental and emotional health. Yet the average adult sleeps for just 6.1 hours on week nights, well below the recommended duration required to maintain a healthy life<sup>1</sup>. Pressures and completing priorities as well as common habits can impact our ability to sleep well but with understanding and practice, strategies can be used to enhance our sleep for a restorative nightâ€™s rest.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Powerful Minds Package </strong>\r\n\r\nStress is consistently in the top 2 self-reported medical conditions of employees across Australia 1 and costs Australian businesses approximately $14.81 billion a year in lost productivity. Stress impacts organisations through decreased productivity, increased risk of error, higher risk of injury and job dissatisfaction leading to high turnover.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThis is a solution-orientated program to provide employees with resources to maintain a healthy physical and mental wellbeing at work and at home. The program aims to help employees identify factors that could contribute to stress, as well as providing skills and tips on how to cope with stressful situations and manage stress effectively.', 'Product', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'product', '', '', '2015-07-07 04:24:54', '2015-07-07 04:24:54', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/?page_id=372', 0, 'page', '', 0),
