(385, 1, '2015-07-07 04:39:10', '2015-07-07 04:39:10', '<div class="col-md-12 sen_me_tem">\r\n<h2>BRIAN MELTZER</h2>\r\n<img class="img-thumbnail img-responsive alignright wp-image-356 size-thumbnail" src="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/BDM-zPhoto-headshot-Dec-2008-150x150.jpg" alt="BDM zPhoto (headshot) Dec 2008" width="150" height="150" />\r\n\r\n<i>B.Com(NZ) M.Ec (Monash) </i>\r\nBrian was chief economist of ICI Australia (now Orica) 1979 -1983 prior to a 25 year career in inve stment banking.\r\nHe was appointed Director of a Federal government licensed Innovations Investment Fund as well as a Federal government licensed technology incubator. He has been a Non Executive Director or Advis\r\nor in a number of private companies in the area of HR, Health and Aged Care, Software, Entertainment and Finance\r\n. He worked with the management of the current SMG Health team during the 15 years that he co-owned OSA Group (later PPC) â€“ a provider of mental health services to large corporates.\r\n<p class="text-justify">Brian is currently a Director of Prana Biotechnology, a company publically listed on both the ASX and Nasdaq, and has served for many years as Chairman of its Audit &amp; Risk committee as well as of its Remuneration committee.</p>\r\n<p class="text-justify">He has regularly taken the role of mentor and business angel in a number of start-ups as well as in mature private businesses.</p>\r\n<p class="text-justify">From 1994 Brian has been a Director of the Australia Israel Chamber of Commerce and since 2011 he has been Chairman of Independence Australia which provides services and products to the Disability and Aged Care sectors.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-12 sen_me_tem"><a href="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-3.png"><img class="img-thumbnail img-responsive alignright wp-image-373 size-thumbnail" src="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-3-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>\r\n<h2>Ian Shakespeare</h2>\r\n<i>MBA BSc MAPS and CEO of SMG Health </i>\r\n\r\nIan Shakespeare MBA BSc MAPS and CEO of SMG Health is a Psychologist &amp; Management Consultant with over 25 yearsâ€™ experience assisting organisations in improving productivity through the implementation of integrated holistic health and wellbeing programs to businesses across the Asia Pacific region. He strongly believes in the importance of individual employees taking responsibility for their own health coupled with need of organisations in creating and maintaining work environments conducive to this. Ian is confident expert staff (physical and mental health) at SMG coupled with their passion and commitment to improved health and productivity outcomes will be critical in achieving our charter: Healthy workplaces = Healthy outcomes\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-12 sen_me_tem">\r\n\r\n<a href="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-1.png"><img class="img-thumbnail img-responsive alignright wp-image-376 size-thumbnail" src="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-1-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>\r\n<h2>Jaqui Bond</h2>\r\n<i>B.App.Sc (Physio), Grad. Dip. Hlth, Research Meth., MPH. </i>\r\n\r\nJaquiâ€™s passion is leading a team to deliver quality driven programs which assist people to be the best they can be. She does this well from experience borne across 25 years in the healthcare industry. She started in clinical physiotherapy and over the years became business owner, strategic program developer and implementer, and team leader. She holds a Masters in Public Health from Columbia University (New York) which provides her with a solid framework for health services management to ensure that not only are the programs right for your employees but also right for your organisation to achieve the goals it seeks.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-12 sen_me_tem">