 src="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-3-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>\r\n\r\nIan Shakespeare MBA BSc MAPS and CEO of SMG Health is a Psychologist &amp; Management Consultant with over 25 yearsâ€™ experience assisting organisations in improving productivity through the implementation of integrated holistic health and wellbeing programs to businesses across the Asia Pacific region. He strongly believes in the importance of individual employees taking responsibility for their own health coupled with need of organisations in creating and maintaining work environments conducive to this. Ian is confident expert staff (physical and mental health) at SMG coupled with their passion and commitment to improved health and productivity outcomes will be critical in achieving our charter: Healthy workplaces = Healthy outcomes\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-12 sen_me_tem">\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Jaqui Bond</h2>\r\n<i>B.App.Sc (Physio), Grad. Dip. Hlth, Research Meth., MPH. </i>\r\n\r\nJaquiâ€™s passion is leading a team to deliver quality driven programs which assist people to be <a href="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-1.png"><img class="img-thumbnail img-responsive alignright wp-image-376 size-thumbnail" src="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-1-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>the best they can be. She does this well from experience borne across 25 years in the healthcare industry. She started in clinical physiotherapy and over the years became business owner, strategic program developer and implementer, and team leader. She holds a Masters in Public Health from Columbia University (New York) which provides her with a solid framework for health services management to ensure that not only are the programs right for your employees but also right for your organisation to achieve the goals it seeks.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-12 sen_me_tem">\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>PHILOMINA GUNASEKERA</h2>\r\n<i>Institute of Chartered Accountants - Australia\r\nChartered Institute of Management Accountants - UK\r\nAssociation of Accounting Technicians â€“ UK </i>\r\n\r\nTwenty five years of work experience in diversified organisations (Public listed, SMEs) which includes <a href="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-5.png"><img class="img-thumbnail img-responsive alignright wp-image-383 size-thumbnail" src="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-5-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>Manufacturing, Stock broking, Real Estate, Financial services, Employee Wellness and Other Professional service sectors as a Senior Member and Head of Finance.\r\n\r\nWorked for A4e Group of Companies as the Finance Director (CFO) and Company Secretary since March 2013. Prior to the above role, worked as the CFO, Director for PPC Worldwide for 11 years (A United Health Group Company, NYSE entity). Key roles included Overseeing all financial activities (whilst overseeing a team) that entailed budgeting, forecasting, month-end reporting, audit, tax, procurement, ERP implementation, mergers and acquisitions. A key part of the role involved aligning finance closely with the business to assist with company performance / activities, strategic direction and business growth.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-12 sen_me_tem">\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Tim</h2>\r\n<i> Senior Commercial Account Manager </i>\r\n\r\nTim is an Exercise Physiologist with a post graduate qualification in Health Promotion. Over the last 15 yea<a href="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-4.png"><img class="img-thumbnail img-responsive alignright wp-image-379 size-thumbnail" src="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-4-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>rs he has designed and managed some of Australiaâ€™s largest and most successful workplace wellness programs. Over the last decade Tim has presented regularly at industry conferences in the areas of Best Practice and Return on Investment in workplace wellness. In his current role as Senior Commercial Account Manager, he is the responsible for the program design and relationship management for major clients throughout Australia and New Zealand as well as the management of SMGâ€™s Commercial Team.â€\r\n\r\nTitle is tricky. Technically current title is â€œCommercial Account Managerâ€. However I want to differentiate my title from CAM, so it carries more weight with clients when issues get escalated â€“ so I have been unofficially using â€œSenior Commercial Account Managerâ€. As background, when Birgit (previous â€˜Health Management MDâ€™ then â€˜Strategic Relationships Managerâ€™) went on Mat leave â€“ I was given higher duties but no title change. Her role was made redundant but this has never been formally announced so had no impact on org structure or my official role / title. My current role includes duties within CAM, Strategic Relationships Manager and Health Management Business Manager.\r\n\r\nSuggestions below but Im happy with any title that fits within org structure so let me know your preference and Il use it from July 1st.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Senior Commercial Account Manager</li>\r\n	<li>National Commercial Manager</li>\r\n	<li>National Relationships Manager</li>\r\n	<li>Business Manager</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Senior Management Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '334-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-07 04:43:49', '2015-07-07 04:43:49', '', 334, 'http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/334-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
