(427, 1, '2015-07-07 08:07:04', '2015-07-07 08:07:04', '<div class="col-md-10">\r\n  <h2>BRIAN MELTZER</h2>\r\n  <i>Chairman  </i> \r\n\r\n  <p class="text-justify">Brian was chief economist of ICI Australia (now Orica) 1979 -1983 prior to a 25 year career in investment banking. He was appointed Director of a Federal government licensed Innovations Investment Fund  as well as a Federal government licensed technology incubator. He has been a Non-Executive Director or Advisor in a number of private companies in the area of HR, Health and Aged Care, Software, Entertainment and Finance. He\r\n worked with the management of the current SMG Health team during the 15 years that he co-owned OSA Group (later PPC) â€“ a provider of mental health services to large corporates.</p>\r\n   \r\n <p class="text-justify">Brian is currently a Director of Prana Biotechnology, a company publically listed on both the ASX and Nasdaq, and has served for many years as Chairman of its Audit & Risk committee as well as of its Remuneration committee.</p>\r\n \r\n <p class="text-justify">He has regularly taken the role of mentor and business angel in a number of start-ups as well as in mature private businesses.\r\nFrom 1994 Brian has been a Director of the Australia Israel Chamber of Commerce and since 2011 he has been Chairman of Independence Australia which provides services and products to the Disability and Aged Care sectors</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2"> <img class="img-thumbnail img-responsive alignright wp-image-356 size-thumbnail" src="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/BDM-zPhoto-headshot-Dec-2008-150x150.jpg" alt="BDM zPhoto (headshot) Dec 2008" width="150" height="150" /></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="col-md-10 sen_me_tem">\r\n  <h2>Ian Shakespeare</h2>\r\n  <p><i>Chief Executive Officer</i></p>\r\n<p class="text-justify">Ian Shakespeare MBA BSc MAPS  and CEO of SMG Health is a Psychologist & Management Consultant with over 25 yearsâ€™ experience assisting organisations in improving productivity through the implementation of integrated holistic health and wellbeing programs to businesses across the Asia Pacific region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="text-justify">He strongly believes in the importance of individual employees taking responsibility for their own health coupled with need of organisations in creating and maintaining work environments conducive to this.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="text-justify">Ian is confident expert staff (physical and mental health) at SMG coupled with their passion and commitment to improved health and productivity outcomes will be critical in achieving our charter: Healthy workplaces = Healthy outcomes </p>\r\n    </div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 sen_me_tem" >  <a href="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-3.png"><img class="img-thumbnail img-responsive alignright wp-image-373 size-thumbnail" src="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-3-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a></div>\r\n<div class="col-md-10 sen_me_tem">\r\n  <h2>Jaqui Bond</h2>\r\n <p> <i>Operations Director </i> </p>\r\n \r\n<p class="text-justify">B.App.Sc (Physio), Grad. Dip. Hlth, Research Meth., MPH.</p>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<p class="text-justify">Jaquiâ€™s passion is leading a team to deliver quality driven programs which assist people to be the best they can be.  She does this well from experience borne across 25 years in the healthcare industry. She started in clinical physiotherapy and over the years became business owner, strategic program developer and implementer,  and team leader. She holds a Masters in Public Health from Columbia University (New York) which provides her with a solid framework for health services management to ensure that not only are the programs right for your employees but also right for your organisation to achieve the goals it seeks.</p>\r\n </div>\r\n <div class="col-md-2 sen_me_tem"><a href="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-1.png"><img class="img-thumbnail img-responsive alignright wp-image-376 size-thumbnail" src="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-1-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a></div>\r\n \r\n<div class="col-md-10 sen_me_tem">\r\n  <h2>Philomina Gunasekera</h2>\r\n <p> <i>Chief Financial Officer</i>/<p>\r\n \r\n<p class="text-justify">Twenty five years of work experience in diversified organisations (Public listed, SMEs) which includes Manufacturing, Stock broking, Real Estate, Financial services, Employee Wellness and Other Professional service sectors as a Senior Member and Head of Finance.</p>\r\n<p class="text-justify">Previous experiences include A4e Group of Companies as the Finance Director (CFO) and Company Secretary since for 2 years. Prior to that worked as the CFO, Director for PPC Worldwide for 11 years (A United Health Group Company, NYSE entity).</p>\r\n<p class="text-justify">Key roles included overseeing all financial activities (whilst overseeing a team) that entailed budgeting, forecasting, month-end reporting, audit, tax, procurement, ERP implementation, mergers and acquisitions. A key part of the role involved aligning finance closely with the business to assist with company performance / activities, strategic direction and business growth. </p>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Philomina-Gunasekera-CV-Template.doc">Read More</a>\r\n\r\n\r\n </div>\r\n  <div class="col-md-2 sen_me_tem"><a href="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-5.png"><img class="img-thumbnail img-responsive alignright wp-image-383 size-thumbnail" src="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-5-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a></div>\r\n<div class="col-md-10 sen_me_tem">\r\n  <h2>Tim Nelson</h2>\r\n <p> <i> Head of Sales</i></p> \r\n <p class="text-justify">Tim is an Exercise Physiologist with a post graduate qualification in Health Promotion. Over the last 15 years he has designed and managed some of Australiaâ€™s largest and most successful workplace wellness programs. Over the last decade Tim has presented regularly at industry conferences in the areas of Best Practice and Return on Investment in workplace wellness. In his current role as Head of Sales, Tim is responsible for the program design and relationship management for major clients throughout Australia and New Zealand as well as the management of SMGâ€™s Commercial Team</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 sen_me_tem"><a href="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-4.png"><img class="img-thumbnail img-responsive alignright wp-image-379 size-thumbnail" src="http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/team-4-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a></div>\r\n', 'Senior Management Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '334-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-07 08:07:04', '2015-07-07 08:07:04', '', 334, 'http://111.93.163.213/SMGHealth/php/334-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
